{"author":{"id":"df79d9acb56ef89cd944cc8548377a5d54d09f0704d032bd86e5f202c0cd02f7"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1494863068,"nonce":"f7InqcjTY7VMu8dePwPSZBkylus=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDEwODI1MTEwNDg="},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":5,"timestamp":1494863068,"nonce":"UfQU7UHqAyaL6nxygSqQuSAywAg=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDEwODI1MTEwNDk="},"added":["planning"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1494863208,"nonce":"Az3pcRjbI8oaK2gKtXHJU9b6nVA=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwMTUxNjM0OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1308#issuecomment-301516349"},"message":"Right now my personal TravisCI setup have a build matrix testing against Galaxy dev and stable, and one of these will also deploy to the Test Tool Shed. This seems a perfect example for using a deployment stage - I'll post back once that's working.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1494950368,"nonce":"d5yCUY9dF3Nzi0Pg+0UiEZw4XoQ=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwMTgyOTI1OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1308#issuecomment-301829258"},"message":"This took a few false starts, but I got it working for a multi-test stage (against Galaxy master and dev branches) then single deploy stage (to the Test Tool Shed if on right branch):\n\nhttps://github.com/peterjc/pico_galaxy/commit/4506825607ec5848e7663f2c6363fb1407f74498\nhttps://travis-ci.org/peterjc/pico_galaxy/builds/232879541\n\nThe key point for me was appreciating that my test stage's ``before_install``, ``install``, ``script`` (etc) defined at top level would by default also be applied to my new stages. I had to define (dummy) entries for those as well.\n\nIn solving this the \"View Configuration\" tag next to the \"Job Log\" shown for a build was really helpful.","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1495118935,"nonce":"f0gPm5+l0nz28kz6WoXc4TqEw2Y=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwMjQyNzA1MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1308#issuecomment-302427051"},"message":"A slightly more complicated version with three stages:\n\n* Lint (one build, but might be useful to run Python pep8/flake8 checks under Python 2 and 3)\n* Test (two builds for Galaxy master and dev branches - could target specific releases)\n* Deploy (one build)\n\nhttps://travis-ci.org/peterjc/pico_galaxy/builds/233622432\n\nGiven the linting itself is very quick, this is perhaps overkill as installing planemo just for linting is a considerable overhead - doing the linting in each test build is probably quicker overall.","files":null}]}